What Salesforce does about it

There's a hard ceiling: System.LimitException: Maximum trigger depth exceeded at 16 levels of nesting. This is uncatchable and rolls back the entire transaction.

But hitting depth 16 is the lucky outcome. The common failure is subtler — you don't recurse infinitely, you recurse two or three times, and each pass creates a duplicate Task, or increments a counter, or re-queries. No exception, just wrong data. Plus every pass consumes from the same shared governor budget: 100 SOQL, 150 DML, 10s CPU for the whole transaction regardless of depth.
