Best: make the logic idempotent

Guards are a patch. The robust answer is logic that's safe to run twice because it checks whether the thing it cares about actually changed:

public static void syncContactsOnRename(List<Account> newAccts, Map<Id, Account> oldMap) {

    Set<Id> renamedIds = new Set<Id>();

    for (Account a : newAccts) {
        // the guard IS the change check
        if (a.Name != oldMap.get(a.Id).Name) {
            renamedIds.add(a.Id);
        }
    }

    if (renamedIds.isEmpty()) return;   // second pass exits here naturally
    // ...
}

